('Onion Achcharu in Jaffna', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/6a-2.jpg', 'Shallots/Small Onion – 500g,  (After peel)Carrot – 200g, Butter Bonchi – 200g, Banana Pepper – 150g, Dates – 200g, Green chili – 100g, Garlic cloves – 7 or 8, Ginger – Medium size (About the size of 2 garlic cloves), Mustard seeds – 50g, Sugar – 50g, Dried red chili – 30g, Vinegar – 300ml, Salt – As you want', 'Peel the shallots and get ready with all other ingredients as above.Firstly, wash all the vegetables. Then cut the carrot, banana pepper, and butter bonchi. Also, cut the tail part of green chilies. Put everything along with the onions on a flat surface and dry them for one or two hours. We usually dry them under the sunlight. If that’s hard dry them under the fan.Grind mustard seeds, dried red chilies, ginger, garlic, 50g of dates, and vinegar to a paste. (You don’t need to grind them to a smooth paste) Then, add sugar and salt to it. Mix them well.So now you have the ground paste, 150g of dates, and dried vegetables.Put everything in a large container and mix them well until all are combined.Once done, leave them in the same container for four to five hours. Then, again give a good mix and put them in an air-tight glass bottle for everyday use.This is how to make onion achcharu in Jaffna style. Serve and enjoy this best onion achcharu with rice/pittu/string hoppers and curries.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '45'),
('Pumpkin Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/10a.jpg', 'Pumpkin – 1kg, Onion – 100g, Green chili – 2 or 3, Dried red chili – 2 or 3, Garlic clove – 3 or 4, Turmeric powder – ½  teaspoon, Cumin seeds – ½ teaspoon, Mustard seeds – ½ teaspoon, Black Pepper – ½ teaspoon, Thick coconut milk – 150ml, Water – 200ml, Curry leaves – Few, Salt – As you want, Cooking oil – As you want', 'Take the pumpkin, rinse it well, and cut it into medium-sized pieces. Also, chop the onions and dry red chilies. Additionally, slice the green chilies and get ready with garlic, curry leaves, mustard seeds, cumin seeds, black pepper, turmeric powder, and salt. Prepare the thick coconut milk and take some water.Grind cumin seeds, black pepper, and garlic together to a paste. You don’t need to grind them to a smooth paste.Now, place the cooking skillet over the stove and put the pumpkin pieces in it. On top of that, add green chilies, 20% of the chopped onion, turmeric powder, salt, and water. Give a good mix.Cook covered under high flame for 10 minutes.Open the lid, give a good stir, and again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates and the pumpkin turns tender. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Now, mash the pumpkin pieces a bit.Add the ground mixture and coconut milk. Stir and mix well under low flame for a minute. Switch off the flame and keep it aside for final preparation.Heat the oil in a deep-fried pan and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then, add the curry leaves and dried red chilies. Sauté those for 30 seconds and then add the remaining 80% of onions. Sauté those until onions start to turn golden.Now, add this fried mix to the pumpkin curry. Mix well until all combined.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a Sri Lankan pumpkin curry recipe with coconut milk. Serve and enjoy this delicious pumpkin curry recipe.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '40'),
('Jackfruit Seed Fry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/6a.jpg', 'Jackfruit Seeds – 250g, Turmeric Powder – ½ teaspoon, Red Chili Powder – ½ teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Cooking Oil – As you want', 'Take the jackfruit seeds and boil them in water for 10 minutes.Now, let the jackfruit seeds to go room temperature. Then, cut them into half and peel off the skin.Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix them well.Heat the oil and fry jackfruit seeds until they start to turn golden. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under high flame.Finally, add some chili powder and mix well till all are combined.This is how to make the best Sri Lankan jackfruit seeds fry recipe at home. Serve and enjoy these deep-fried crispy and spicy jackfruit seeds.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '20'),
('Eggplant Potato Tomato Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/9a.jpg', 'Eggplant – 400g, Potato – 400g, Tomato – 200g, Banana pepper – 100g, Onion – 150g, Garlic – 6 or 7, Curry powder – 3 tablespoons, Fenugreek seeds – ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Mustard seeds – ½ teaspoon, Thick coconut milk – 100ml, Thin coconut milk – 600ml, Thin tamarind juice – 200ml, Curry leaves – Few, Salt – As you want, Cooking oil – As you want', 'Clean, rinse, and cut eggplants, potatoes, tomatoes, and banana peppers into large pieces. Also, slice the garlic and chop the onion. Besides, get ready with mustard seeds, fenugreek seeds, curry powder, turmeric powder, salt, and curry leaves. In addition, prepare thick coconut milk, thin coconut milk, and tamarind juice.Heat the oil and fry eggplant, potato, and banana pepper separately. Before fry, add some salt to each vegetable and mix.Fry them until starts turn golden. For me, it takes about five minutes to eggplant, five minutes to potato, and four minutes to banana pepper under high flame.Heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then, add onion and curry leaves. Sauté them till onion turn translucent. Now, add garlic and fenugreek seeds. Sauté them till the onion turns to a golden brown.Now add the tomatoes, turmeric powder, salt, curry powder, tamarind juice, and thin coconut milk. Give a good mix.Cook covered under high flame for six minutes.Now add the fried vegetables and thick coconut milk. Give a good gentle mix.Cook covered under low flame for about five minutes.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a delicious eggplant potato tomato curry recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style spicy brinjal Aloo tomato curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '45'),
('Green Chilli Coconut Sambal (Pol Sambol)', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/6a-2.jpg', 'Grated coconut – 200g, Onion – 50g, Green chili – 10 to 12, Thick tamarind juice – 1 ½ tablespoon, Sugar – ½ teaspoon, Salt – As you need (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt)', 'Get ready with grated coconut, onions, green chilies, thick tamarind juice, sugar, and salt.Clean the mortar and pestle. Add green chilies and salt together. Using the pestle bash and muddle them to a fine/medium textured paste. For me, it takes about 4 minutes.Now add the tamarind juice and bash them for a minute.Then add grated coconut and sugar. Bash and muddle them until all combined well. For me, it takes about 3 minutes.Finally, add the onions and bash them for one or two minutes. You don’t have to bash the onions to smooth texture, because this green chilli coconut sambal is tastier when onion pieces locate here and there.This is how to make the best green chilli coconut sambal recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this keto-friendly green pol sambol.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '15'),
('Agathi Keerai Sodhi', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/6a.jpg', 'Agathi keerai – 75g, Onion – 75g, Green chili – 3 or 4, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Semi thick coconut milk – 500ml, Thick tamarind juice – 50ml, Water – 300ml, Salt – As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt)', 'Take the Agathi keerai and wash them thoroughly. Also, prepare coconut milk, tamarind juice, and take some water. Additionally, get ready with chopped onions, sliced green chilies, turmeric powder, and salt.Take a skillet and place the Agathi keerai in it. On top of that, add onions, green chilies, turmeric powder, salt, tamarind juice, and water.Cook covered under high flame for five minutes.Take off the lid, give a good mix, and again cook covered under high flame for about three minutes.Now add the coconut milk and cook uncovered under high flame for one or two minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid foaming the milk.Taste the Sodhi and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a simple Agathi keerai Sodhi recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style traditional Agathi keerai Sodhi.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '20'),
('Tomato Sodhi', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/9a-1.jpg', 'Tomato – 150g, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Fenugreek seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Onion – 30g, Curry leaves – Few, Green chili – 3 or 4, Lime – ½, Thin coconut milk – 350ml, Thick coconut milk – 200ml, Salt – As you wish (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt)', 'Cut the tomato into medium size pieces. Also, slice the green chilies and chop the onions. Besides, get ready with lime, curry leaves, fenugreek seeds, turmeric powder, and salt.Prepare the thin and thick coconut milk.In a cooking pot add tomato, turmeric powder, fenugreek seeds, salt, onion, curry leaves, green chilies, and thin coconut milk. Give a mix and switch on the flame.Cook covered under high flame for about five to six minutes. If the milk foams up reduce the flame and give a good stir.Now add the thick coconut milk and cook uncovered under medium flame for about two minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid foaming.Finally, switch off the flame and add the lime juice. Also, taste and adjust salt if needed.This is the easy and best way to make Tomato Sodhi recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style vegan sothi.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '30'),
('Bitter Gourd Fry with Curd Sambol', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7.jpg', 'Bitter Gourd – 400g, Onion – 150g, Green chili – 3 or 4, Coriander leaves – As you want, Curd – 2 tablespoons, Turmeric powder – ¼ teaspoon, Salt – As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt), Cooking oil – As you want (KETO people use the Organic Coconut Oil)', 'Rinse the bitter gourd and cut it into thin round pieces. Take off the middle part along with the seeds. Also, chop the onions, coriander leaves, and green chilies. Besides, take turmeric powder, curd, salt, and cooking oil.Add turmeric powder and salt to the bitter gourd. Mix those well until all are combined.Heat the oil and fry the bitter gourd pieces to a golden brown. For me, it takes about 10 minutes under high flame.Now take a large bowl and add onion, green chili, coriander leaves, curd, and salt. Mix them well.Finally, add fried bitter gourd pieces and mix everything till combined.This is how to make a simple bitter gourd fry with curd sambol recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan healthy pavakkai or Karawila fried salad.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Sambar Recipe without Sambar Powder & Coconut Milk', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/8a.jpg', 'Potato – 100g, Pumpkin – 100g, Carrot – 100g, Eggplant – 100g, Tomato – 100g, Drumstick – 100g, Onion – 100g, Dhal – 200g, Coriander leaves – As you need, Green chili – 2 or 3, Dried red chili – 2 or 3, Garlic clove – 3 or 4, Curry leaves – Few, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Mustard seeds – ½ teaspoon, Curry powder – 1 tablespoon, Thin tamarind juice – 200ml, Water – As you want (I used 2000ml), Salt – As you need, Cooking oil – As you need', 'Clean and slice the potato, pumpkin, carrot, eggplant, tomato, drumstick, onion, garlic, green chili, dried red chili, and coriander leaves. Besides, rinse the dhal and prepare tamarind juice. Apart from that, get ready with water, curry leaves, turmeric powder, mustard seeds, curry powder, salt, and cooking oil.Heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then add onion, green chili, dried red chili, and curry leaves. Sauté them till the onion starts turn to golden.Now, add dhal, garlic, turmeric powder, salt, and water. Give a good mix.Cook covered under the high flame until dhal turns tender. For me, it takes about 20 minutes.Now, add potato, pumpkin, carrot, eggplant, tomato, drumstick, curry powder, and tamarind juice. Give a good mix.Cook covered under the high flame until all the vegetables, especially carrots and potatoes turn tender and soft. For me, it takes about 30 minutes. Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.Finally, add the coriander leaves and give a good mix.This is how to make the best sambar recipe without sambar powder and coconut milk. Serve and enjoy this simple Sri Lankan mixed vegetable dish.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '55'),
('Cassava Curry with Coconut Milk', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/10a.jpg', 'Tapioca/Cassava – 1250g, Onion – 125g, Green chili – 3 or 4, Lime – ½, Fenugreek seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Curry leaves – Few, Salt – As you want, Thick coconut milk – 200ml, Water – 600ml', 'Take the cassava, peel off the skin, rinse well, and cut them into small pieces as shown in the picture below.Chop the onion and slice the green chili. Also, get ready with lime, curry leaves, turmeric powder, fenugreek seeds, and salt.Prepare the coconut milk and take some water.Now place the skillet on the stove and add cassava. On top of that, add turmeric powder, fenugreek seeds, salt, onion, green chili, and curry leaves. Mix them well.Cook covered under high flame for about 10 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good mix, and again cook covered under high flame till cassava turns tender. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Using a spoon mash the cassava as shown in the picture below.Now add the coconut milk, mix well, and cook uncovered under medium flame for about a minute.Finally, switch off the flame and squeeze the lime. Give one last good mix. Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the best Sri Lankan cassava curry with coconut milk. Serve and enjoy this simple tapioca milky curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '35'),
('Snake Gourd Curry with Milk for Rice', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9a.jpg', 'Snake gourd – 350g, Thick coconut milk – 175ml, Onion – 50g, Green chili – 2 or 3, Curry leaves – Few, Turmeric powder – ¼ teaspoon, Salt – As you wish, Cooking oil – 2 tablespoons', 'Take the snake gourd, peel the skin off and wash it thoroughly.Chop the snake gourd into small pieces.Extract the thick coconut milk. Also, chop the onion and slice the green chili. In addition, get ready with curry leaves, salt, and turmeric powder.Place the cooking pan on the stove. First of all, add the chopped snake gourd. Also, add onion, green chili, curry leaves, salt, and turmeric powder. On top of that, add the cooking oil. Mix everything well.Switch on the flame and cook covered under medium flame for 4 to 6 minutes.Take off the lid, stir, and mix everything. Now cook uncovered under medium flame until the snake gourd gets little fry. Stir occasionally to avoid burn. For me, it takes about a minute.Finally, add thick coconut milk and mix everything. Cook covered under low flame for 3 to 5 minutes.Open the lid and taste the curry. Adjust salt if needed.This is how to make snake gourd curry for rice. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style snake gourd milk curry recipe.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '35'),
('Jaffna Traditional Pol Sambal', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/7a.jpg', 'Grated coconut – 6 full tablespoons, Dried red chili – 6 to 8, Shallot/Small onion – 50g, Tamarind – Small portion with 3 or 4 seeds, Sugar – ½ teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Water – 1 or 2 teaspoons', 'Grate the coconut and peel off the skin of shallots. Besides, get ready with dried red chili, tamarind, sugar, salt, and water.Clean the grinding stone and roller. Firstly, add dried red chilies, salt, and a little water (About a teaspoon of water). Grind them to a smooth paste by moving the roller back and forth direction.Now, add tamarind, bash a bit using the roller, and take out the seeds carefully. Again move the roller back and forth direction for 1 or 2 minutes.Then, add sugar and move the roller until all combined.Add the grated coconut and move the roller back and forth direction until totally mixed. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Finally, add the shallots and bash them a bit.Again move the roller back and forth direction until all combined.In the end, using your fingers take off all the coconut sambol. This is how to make the best and tasty Ammikallu Red coconut sambol recipe.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '15'),
('Bonchi Recipe', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/12a.jpg', 'Green Bean/Bonchi – 150g, Onion – 50g, Green chili – 2 or 3, Turmeric powder – Less than ¼ teaspoon, Water – 75ml, Thick coconut milk – 100ml, Curry leaves – Few, Cooking oil – As you need, Salt – As you need', 'Take the green bean and wash it thoroughly. Cut them into 2-inch pieces.Chop the onions and slice the green chilies. Also, get ready with curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt.Prepare 100ml of thick coconut milk. Also, get ready with 75ml of water.Heat the oil in a cooking pan and add the onion. Sauté it until it gets translucent. Then add green chilies and curry leaves. Stir and cook for a minute.Now add the sliced green bean, mix well, and cook covered under low flame for 2 or 3 minutes.Take off the lid. Add turmeric powder, salt, and water. Mix everything well.Cook covered under medium flame for 2 minutes.Take the lid off and add thick coconut milk. Mix well.Again cook covered under low flame for 2 minutes.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the best green bean coconut milk curry recipe. Serve and enjoy this delicious Sri Lankan bonchi curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Bitter Gourd Sambol', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/6a-1.jpg', 'Bitter Gourd – 600g, Onion – 250g, Green chili – 5 or 6, Thick coconut milk – 4 tablespoons, Very thick tamarind juice – 2 tablespoons, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Sugar – 1 teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Cooking oil – As you want', 'Rinse the bitter gourd and cut it into thin round pieces. Take off the middle part along with the seeds. Also, chop the onions and green chilies. Besides, prepare the coconut milk and tamarind juice. Additionally, take sugar, turmeric powder, salt, and cooking oil.Add turmeric powder and salt to the bitter gourd. Mix those well until all combined.Heat the oil in a deep-fry pan and fry the bitter gourd pieces to a golden brown. For me, it takes about 10 minutes under high flame.Now take a large bowl and add onion, green chili, coconut milk, tamarind juice, sugar, and salt. Mix them well.Finally, add fried bitter gourd pieces and mix everything until totally combined.This is how to make the best bitter gourd sambol recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan pavakkai or Karawila fried salad.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '35'),
('Tomato Chutney Recipe for Dosa/Idli/Chapati/Paratha', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/9a.jpg', 'Tomato – 350g, Onion – 100g, Dried red chili – 5 or 6, Curry leaves – Few, Mustard seeds – 1 teaspoon, Fennel seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Salt – As you need, Cooking oil – As you need', 'Slice the onion and tomato. Also, get ready with dried red chilies, curry leaves, mustard seeds, fennel seeds, and salt.Heat the oil in a cooking pan. Add ¼ teaspoon of mustard seeds and let it splutter. Now add the onions and fry them for one minute under high flame.Then add the curry leave and fry them for another one minute under high flame.Add dried red chilies and fennel seeds. Stir and fry them for one more minute under medium flame.Finally, add tomatoes and salt.Cook uncovered under medium flame for 6 to 8 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.Now switch off the flame and let the mixture cool down. Then, add the mixture to the food processor and grind it to the semi-smooth paste.Heat a little oil in the same cooking pan and add the rest of the mustard seeds. Let them splutter.Now add the ground mixture and mix them well.Switch off the flame and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make an easy tomato chutney recipe for dosa/idli/chapati/paratha. Serve and enjoy this red tomato chutney with your friends and family.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '20'),
('Cabbage Potato Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/7a-1.jpg', 'Cabbage – 1kg, Potato – 250g, Onion – 150g, Green chili – 3 or 4, Curry leaves – Few, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Thick coconut milk – 250ml, Cooking oil – 2 tablespoons', 'Rinse the cabbage and shred it into tiny pieces. Also, peel off the potato skin and cut it into small pieces. Additionally, chop the onion and green chili. Besides, prepare the coconut milk and get ready with curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt.Now, place a large skillet on the stove and put the cabbage in it. On top of that, add potato, onion, green chili, curry leaves, turmeric powder, salt, and cooking oil.Give a good mix and switch on the flame. Cook covered under high flame for 7 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good stir, and again cook covered under medium flame until potato pieces turn tender. For me, it takes about 7 minutes.Now, add thick coconut milk and mix well.Cook covered under medium flame for 2 minutes. Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to prepare the best Sri Lankan cabbage potato curry recipe. Serve and enjoy this simple cabbage potato milky curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '40'),
('Chickpea', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6a.jpg', 'Chickpeas – 250g, Water – As needed, Onion – 150g, Dried red chili – 2 or 3, Mustard seeds – ½ teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Curry leaves – Few, Cooking oil – As you want', 'Take the chickpeas and soak them overnight in the water. Then wash them thoroughly at least 2 or 3 times.Now add chickpeas, salt, and water in a pressure cooker and cook them until chickpeas turn tender. I leave them to cook until 8 whistles in the pressure cooker.Once done, leave the pressure cooker to remain covered until it comes to room temperature. Then open the lid and strain the water completely using a colander. Besides, slice the onion, dried red chilies, and curry leaves as shown in the picture below. Also, get ready with mustard seeds and cooking oil.Heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then add onion, dried red chili, and curry leaves. Sauté them till onion start turns to golden.Now add the boiled chickpeas and mix them well until all combined.This is how to make an easy Sri Lankan chickpea breakfast recipe. Serve and enjoy this simple vegan chickpeas salad with your friends and family.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '15'),
('Jaffna Ash Plantain Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/11a-1.jpg', 'Ash plantain – 400g, Onion – 50g, Thin coconut milk – 200ml, Thick coconut milk – 100ml, Green chili – 4 or 5, Lime – ½, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Curry leaves – Few, Salt – As you need', 'Take the ash plantains and wash them well.Chop the onion and slice the green chilies. Also, get ready with lime, curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt.Peel off the skin of the ash plantains and cut them into small pieces. Also, prepare the thin coconut milk and thick coconut milk.Now place the cooking wok on the stove. Add ash plantain, onion, green chili, curry leaves, salt, and turmeric powder.Also, add the thin coconut milk and mix them well. Now switch on the flame.Cook covered under high flame for 6 to 8 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good stir, and again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid disappears. For me, it takes about 4 minutes.Now, mash the ash plantains using a spoon.Add the thick coconut milk, give a good mix, and switch off the flame.Finally, add the lime juice and give one last mix.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the Jaffna ash plantain curry at home. Serve and enjoy this delicious ash plantain milky curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Leftover Rice', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/7a.jpg', 'Pazhaya soru/Leftover rice – 2 cups, Water – 500ml, Semi thick coconut milk – 350ml, Onion (Shallots) – 100g, Green chili – 2, Lime – ½, Salt – As you want', 'Take the leftover steamed rice and add water in it. Cover and leave it overnight, at least 8 hours.On the next day morning, take the fermented leftover rice. Besides, chop the onions and green chilies. Apart from that, prepare the coconut milk and take the salt along with lime.Now, smash and squeeze the fermented leftover steamed rice using your fingers.Add onion, green chili, and salt. Again mix, smash, and squeeze everything using your fingers.Finally, add coconut milk and lime.Give one last good mix using a ladle.This is how to make the best Jaffna style pazhaya soru kanji recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan healthy neeragaram dish.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '10'),
('Beetroot Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/9a.jpg', 'Beetroot – 250g (After pealing of the skin), Onion – 50g, Green chili – 2 to 4, Thin coconut milk – 150ml, Turmeric powder – ¼ teaspoon, Salt – As you want, Curry leaves – Few, Cooking oil – 2 tablespoons', 'Take the beetroot and peel off the skin. Wash it well and cut it into small pieces.Chop the onion and slice the green chilies. Also, get ready with coconut milk, curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt.Place the pan on the stove and add the beetroot. Also, add onions, green chilies, curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt. On top of that add two tablespoons of cooking oil. Mix everything well and switch on the flame.Cook covered under the high flame for 2 to 4 minutes.Take off the lid, stir and mix. Again cook covered under medium flame for 2 to 4 minutes.Add the thin coconut milk and mix it up.Cook covered under low flame for 3 to 5 minutes.Take off the lid and taste the curry. Adjust salt if needed.This is how to make an easy beetroot curry recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style delicious beetroot curry with coconut milk for rice.', 'vegetarian', 'nonspicy', '30'),
('Pennywort Salad Recipe with Carrot | Gotu Kola', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/8a.jpg', 'Pennywort/Centella Asiatica/Gotu Kola/Vallarai – 50g, Carrot – 100g, Onion – 40g, Green chili – 3 to 5, Grated coconut – 2 tablespoons, Salt – As you need, Lime – ½', 'Take the bunch of pennyworts and a carrot. Clean and wash them well. Scrape the carrot using a scrapper and chop the pennywort.Chop the onion and green chilies. Also, get ready with grated coconut, salt, and lime.Take the bowl and add scraped carrot and chopped pennywort. On top of that, add onion, green chili, grated coconut, and salt.Mix them well using a spoon.Finally, add the lime juice and give a good mix until all combined.Taste the salad and adjust salt or lime if needed.This is how to male easy pennywort salad recipe with carrot, onion, and grated coconut.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Beans Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/15a.jpg', 'Long Beans – 300g, Onion – 75g, Garlic Cloves – 3 or 4, Curry Leaves – Few, Curry Powder – 1 ½ tablespoon, Thin coconut Milk – 200ml, Thin tamarind Juice – 100ml, Mustard Seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Fenugreek Seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Salt – As you need, Cooking Oil – As you need', 'Take the long beans and cut it into about 2-inch sized pieces. Wash it well and keep aside.Extract coconut milk and prepare the tamarind juice.Chop the onions, slice the garlic and take some curry leaves. Also, get ready with mustard seeds, fenugreek seeds, salt, and curry powder., Heat the oil in a deep-fry pan and fry the pieces of long beans. Fry everything until its color turns into light brown.Now neat the oil in cooking pan and add mustard seeds. Let it splutter.Add the onion and sauté it until it turns into soften and translucent. Then add garlic cloves, curry leaves, and fenugreek seeds. Fry them until the onion turns into golden color.Add the coconut milk and the tamarind juice.Add salt and curry powder. Mix everything well.Cook covered under the high flame for 4 to 6 minutes.Take off the lid and add the fried long beans. Mix everything well and cook covered under low flame for 2 to 4 minutes. If you don’t like thick gravy curry, it’s enough to cook 1 or 2 minutes.Take off the lid and taste the curry. Adjust salt and tamarind juice if needed.This is how to make long beans curry. Serve and enjoy this spicy and thick long beans curry in Sri Lanka style.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '50'),
('Mixed Vegetable Roti Recipe', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/14a.jpg', 'All-purpose flour – 1kg, Green bean – 40g, Carrot – 50g, Leeks – 50g, Green chili – 50g, Onion – 175g, Grated coconut – 200g, Baking powder – 1 teaspoon, Sugar – 1 tablespoon, Salt – As you wish, Water – 400ml, Cooking oil – 4 tablespoons', 'Take the green bean, leeks, carrots, green chilies, and onions. Clean and wash them well. Chop them into small pieces.Get ready with grated coconut, salt, sugar, baking powder, and water.Take a large bowl and add all purpose flour. Also, add salt, baking powder, and sugar. Mix them well till totally combined.Now add carrot, green bean, leeks, green chili, onion, and grated coconut.Mix them well and add the water.Mix everything well using your fingers, knuckles, and palm.Knead the dough for 4 or 5 minutes. The dough should smooth and soft. Add water or flour as needed to adjust consistency.Now add the cooking oil.Again knead the dough for 1 or 2 minutes. The dough should smooth and elastic but not sticky.Now make the balls as you want and keep them aside for at least 1 hour before making the roti.Grease a little oil on a floured surface. On the floured surface, use the rolling pin to roll out the balls until very thin.Heat the skillet and place the thin dough layer on it. Flip and cook on the other side. It took one minute for each side under low flame.This is how to make mixed vegetable roti recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style simple vegetarian roti.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '50'),
('Moringa Leaf Coconut', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/9a.jpg', 'Drumstick leaves – 100g, Grated coconut – 3 tablespoons, Onion – 50g, Green chili – 1 or 2, Dried red chili – 1 or 2, Mustard seeds – ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder – 2 Pinches, Cooking oil – 1 tablespoon, Salt – As you wish', 'Take the bunch of fresh drumstick leaves and separate the leaves from the stalk. Chop the leaves and wash it in the water.Chop the onions, green chilies, and dried red chilies. Also, get ready with mustard seeds, salt, turmeric powder, and grated coconut.Add salt and turmeric powder to the chopped drumstick leaves. Mix it well and leave it aside.Heat the oil in a cooking pan and add mustard seeds. Let it splutter. Then add onions, green chilies, and dried red chilies. Sauté it until the onion turns into golden color. For me, it takes about 2 minutes.Now add the drumstick leaves, mix well, and cook covered under low flame for 2 to 4 minutes.Take off the lid, stir, mix, and cook uncovered under low flame for another 2 to 4 minutes. During this time you should stir constantly to avoid burn.Now add the grated coconut. Stir constantly and cook uncovered under low flame for 1 or 2 minutes.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the delicious drumstick leaves stir fry with grated coconut. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lanka style healthy vegan dish.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '30'),
('Banana Pepper Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/1a-2.jpg', 'My Favorite Combo 1: This Recipe + Rice + Dal Curry + Cabbage FryFavorite Combo 2: This Recipe + Pittu + Dal CurryFavorite Combo 3: This Recipe + Bread + Dal Curry + Sambol', 'Take the banana peppers and wash them well. In each banana pepper make two slits lengthwise, keeping the stem on.Chop the onion and slice the garlic cloves. Also, get ready with curry leaves, mustard seeds, curry powder, turmeric powder, and salt. (Refer Note 1)Get ready with the coconut milk and tamarind juice. (Refer Note 2)Heat the oil in a cooking pan and place the banana peppers.Fry them uncovered under medium flame. Make sure to fry every side of the banana peppers. For me, it takes about 3 minutes.Now add curry leaves, onion, mustard seeds, and garlic. Stir and fry uncovered under medium flame for 2 to 4 minutes. (Refer Note 3)Add curry powder, turmeric powder, and salt. (Refer Note 1)Also, add tamarind juice.Add coconut milk, stir, and mix them gently.Cook covered under low flame for 4 to 6 minutes.Take off the lid and taste the curry. Adjust salt if needed.This is how to make spicy banana pepper curry recipe. Serve and enjoy this delicious spicy vegan dish.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '35'),
('Jaffna Style Brinjal Chutney', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/12a-1.jpg', 'Eggplant – 350g, Onion – 50g, Sugar – 1 ¼ tablespoon, Crushed cardamom – 2 to 4, Crushed cinnamon – ½ teaspoon, Ginger paste – ¼ teaspoon, Garlic paste – ½ teaspoon, Chili powder – 1 teaspoon, Turmeric powder – ½ teaspoon, Thick coconut milk – 10 tablespoons, Very thick tamarind juice – 2 tablespoons, Salt – As you wish, Cooking oil – As you need', 'Cut the eggplant into small sized pieces as shown in the picture below and wash them well. Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix them well.Heat the oil in deep fry cooking pot and add the eggplant. Fry them under medium flame until it turns into brown color. For me, it takes about 10 minutes.Get ready with thick coconut milk and very thick tamarind juice.Crush the cardamom and cinnamon. Chop the onions. Also, get ready with ginger paste, garlic paste, salt, sugar, and chili powder.Heat the oil in a cooking pan and add onions. Sauté them until they’re soft and translucent. Then, add cinnamon, cardamom, salt, ginger paste, garlic paste, sugar, and chili powder.Add the tamarind juice. Also, add coconut milk and mix everything well.Cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes. During this time you should stir occasionally.Taste the gravy and add salt if needed.Finally, add the pieces of fried eggplant. Mix everything till totally combined.Serve and enjoy this Jaffna style eggplant chutney recipe.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '50'),
('Bitter Gourd Recipe Curry for Rice', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/1a.jpg', 'Bitter Gourd – 150gOnion – 50gGreen Chili – 2 or 3Garlic Cloves – 2 or 3Curry Leaves – FewThin Coconut Milk – 400mlTamarind Juice – 100mlCurry Powder – 1 ¼ TablespoonFenugreek Seeds – ¼ TeaspoonTurmeric Powder – ¼ TeaspoonSugar – ¼ TeaspoonCooking Oil – 1 TablespoonSalt – As you needWater – As you need', 'Take the bitter gourd and cut it into 2-inch pieces. Take a bowl and add bitter gourd pieces, salt, and water. Leave it to soak for 10 to 15 minutes.Get ready with curry powder, turmeric powder, sugar, fenugreek seeds, and curry leaves. Also, slice the onions, green chilies, and garlic cloves. (Refer Note 1 and Note 2)Get ready with thin coconut milk and tamarind juice. (Refer Note 3)Now take the soaked bitter gourd pieces and rinse it thoroughly in normal water at least 1 or 2 times. Place the cooking pan over the stove. Add the rinsed bitter gourd pieces, curry powder, turmeric powder, sugar, and fenugreek seeds.Also, add sliced onions, garlic cloves, green chilies, and curry leaves.Add one tablespoon of cooking oil.Add tamarind juice.Also, add coconut milk.Mix it well and switch on the flame.Cook covered for 10 to 12 minutes under high flame. Take off the lid, stir and mix everything well.Again cook covered for 8 to 10 minutes under low flame. (Refer Note 4)Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style thick and spicy bitter gourd recipe for rice.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '50'),
('Vegetable Fried Rice without Soy Sauce & Egg', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/14a.jpg', 'Basmati rice – 350gSoy meat – 25g (Optional)Carrot – 100gLeeks – 75gGreen bean – 75gOnion – 125gGarlic paste – 1 teaspoonGinger paste – ¼ teaspoonTurmeric powder – ¼ teaspoonCurry leaves – 2 sprigsSalt – As you wishCooking oil – As you wish', 'Wash the rice and boil it. Add little oil and salt when boiling the rice. The boiled rice should soft but not sticky or soggy.Add soy meat and water in a bowl. Let the soy meat to soak for 30 minutes. Then strain all the water and cut them into half. Add salt, mix them well, and keep it aside.Cut the carrot, onion, green bean, and leek. Also, take some curry leaves.Get ready with garlic paste, ginger paste, turmeric powder, and salt.Heat the oil in deep fry wok and add curry leaves. Stir and fry them for 20 to 30 seconds. Once done, put them on top of the boiled rice.Fry the onion under the high flame until it turns into brown color. For me, it takes about 5 minutes. Put them on top of the rice.Fry the soy meat under the high flame until it turns into light brown. For me, it takes about 3 minutes. Once done, put them on top of the rice.Now, heat the oil in a cooking pan and add green bean. Cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burn. Then, add the carrot and cook uncovered under medium flame for 3 or 4 minutes. Stir occasionally.Add leeks, salt, and turmeric powder. Stir, mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes.Finally, add ginger and garlic pastes. Cook uncovered under medium flame for 1 minute. Stir constantly to avoid burn.Now put the vegetable mixture too on top of the boiled rice. So now you have the boiled rice, fried curry leaves, onions, soy meat, and vegetable mixture.Mix them well till totally combined.Taste the rice and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make vegetable fried rice in a quick and easy way. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style healthy vegetable fried rice without soya sauce and eggs.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '50'),
('Spicy Soya Meat Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/17a.jpg', 'Soya meat packet – 90gOnion – 90gThick coconut milk – 125mlWater – 300mlCurry powder – 1 ½ tablespoonTurmeric powder – ¼ teaspoonMustard seeds – ½ teaspoonGarlic paste – ¾ tablespoonLime – ½Curry leaves – FewSalt – As you need, Cooking oil – As you need', 'Take the soya meat and its spice mix pack.Take a bowl, add soya meat and water. Let the soya meat to soak for at least 30 minutes. Once it gets soaked, wash the soya meat thoroughly at least 2 or 3 times. Keep the spice mix pack aside for final preparation.Extract the thick coconut milk from grated coconut and take the water.Chop the onion and grind the garlic to paste. Also, get ready with curry leaves, lime, mustard seeds, turmeric powder, salt, and curry powder.Heat the oil in a cooking pan and add mustard seeds. Let it splutter. Now, add the onion and sauté until it gets translucent. Then, add the curry leaves and fry them for one minute.Add the garlic paste, stir, and fry everything until the onion gets a golden color.Now add the soaked soya meat. Stir, mix and cook uncovered under the high flame until the soya meat gets little fry. You should stir and mix occasionally to avoid burn. For me, it takes about 3 minutes.Add curry powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Also, add the water and mix everything well.Cook covered under high flame for 3 to 5 minutes.Take off the lid and add the soya meat spice mix pack which comes with the soya meat packet. Also, add the coconut milk.Mix everything well and cook covered under very low flame for 4 to 6 minutes.Take off the lid and switch off the flame. Add lime juice and mix everything well.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.Serve and enjoy this mouthwatering spicy soya meat curry recipe in Sri Lankan style.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '40'),
('Spring Onion Flower', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/8a-2.jpg', 'Spring onion flower - 250g, Grated coconut - 2 tablespoons, Onion - 40g, Green chili - 2 or 3, Turmeric powder - ¼ teaspoon, Salt - As you wish, Cooking oil - 1 tablespoon', 'Take the spring onions flower/Vengaya thal pooChop that into small pieces. Wash it well at least 2 or 3 times. (Refer Note 1)Chop the onion and green chili. Also, get ready with grated coconut, turmeric powder, and salt. (Refer Note 2)Add the chopped spring onion flower in the cooking pan. Also, add green chili, onion, salt, and turmeric powder.Now add one tablespoon of cooking oil.Mix them well and switch on the flame.Cook covered under the high flame for 3 to 5 minutes.Open the lid and cook uncovered under medium flame until the spring onion flower gets little fry. During this time you may stir and mix occasionally to avoid burn. For me, it takes 4 minutes.Finally, add grated coconut, mix, and cook uncovered under low flame for one minute.Taste the curry and add salt if needed.Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style simple spring onion flower recipe with grated coconut.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '10'),
('Eggplant Milk Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/10a-1.jpg', 'Eggplant - 250g, Thick coconut milk - 100ml, Water - 150ml, Onion - 25g, Green chili - 2 or 3, Garlic clove - 1 or 2, Curry leaves - Few, Turmeric powder - ¼ teaspoon, Salt - As you need', 'Take the eggplant, cut it into medium sized pieces, and rinse it well.Chop the onions and slice the green chilies and garlic cloves. Also, take the curry leaves, turmeric powder, salt, and water. Besides, get ready with thick coconut milk. (Refer Note 1)Place the cooking pot over the stove. Add the pieces of eggplant, onions, green chilies, garlic cloves, curry leaves, salt, and turmeric powder.Switch on the flame and add the water. Mix everything well.Cook covered under the high flame for 4 to 6 minutes.Take off the lid, stir and mix everything. Again cook covered under high flame until all the water disappears. For me, it takes about 4 minutes.Now take off the lid and turn the flame to low. Mash the eggplant using a spoon for 1 minute.Add the thick coconut milk and mix well.Cook covered under low flame for 2 to 4 minutes.Take off the lid and taste the curry. Adjust salt if needed. (Refer Note 3)Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style easy eggplant milk curry recipe or Kathirikai paal curry.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '10'),
('Dal Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/13a-2.jpg', 'Dal/Dhal/Parippu - 150g, Onion - 100g, Thin milk - 350ml, Water 400ml, Garlic paste - ½ tablespoon, Dried red chili - 2 or 3, Curry leaves - Few, Mustard seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Cumin seeds - 2 pinches, Fennel seeds - ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you wish, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Take the dal and wash it for 2 or 3 times.Chop the onion and dried red chili. Also, get ready with curry leaves, salt, turmeric powder, mustard seeds, fennel seeds, cumin seeds, and garlic paste.Extract the coconut milk from grated coconut and take some water. (Refer Note 1)Place the cooking pan on the stove and add the dal. Also, add the water.Mix and switch on the flame. Cook uncovered under the high flame for 7 to 9 minutes. During this time the water may foam up, so keep your eye on it. (Refer Note 2)Now add salt and turmeric powder. Mix well and cook uncovered under high flame until the dal gets boiled enough and turns tender. For me, it takes about 3 minutes.Add thin coconut milk and mix well.Cook uncovered under the high flame for 2 to 4 minutes. Now switch off the flame and leave it aside for final preparation.On the other side, heat the oil in a cooking pan. Add mustard seeds and let it splutter.Now add onion, curry leaves, and dried red chili. Stir and fry everything until the onion just starts to turn a golden color.Add fennel seeds, cumin seeds, and garlic paste. Stir and fry them for 30 seconds.Finally, add the prepared dal curry to this fried mix.Mix everything and taste the curry. Adjust salt if needed and switch off the flame. (Refer Note 3)This is how to make dal curry for bread. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style delicious dhal curry with bread.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '15'),
('Coconut Sambal For Dosa', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/12a.jpg', 'Dried red chili - 10 to 15, Grated coconut - 100g, Onion - 30g, Curry leaves - Few, Split skinned black gram/Urad dal - 1 teaspoon, Fennel seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Mustard seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Very thick tamarind juice - 1 ½ teaspoons, Water - 100ml, Cooking oil - As you need, Salt - As you need', 'Get ready with grated coconut, salt, and dried red chilies.Chop the onions, curry leaves, and one or two red chilies. Get ready with mustard seeds, fennel seeds, and urad dal. (Refer Note 1)Extract very thick tamarind juice and take some ordinary water.Now add dried red chilies and salt to the grinder. Grind them together to smooth powder. (Refer Note 2)Add grated coconut and water. Grind them again until all mix together well enough. Keep it aside for final preparation.Heat the oil in a frying pan and add mustard seeds. Let it splutter.Add chopped onions. Cook until the onions turn translucent.Now add chopped curry leaves and dried red chili. Stir and fry for 30 seconds under medium flame.Add urad dal. Stir and fry until the onions turn to little brown color. It may take about 1 minute.Finally, add fennel seeds. Stir and fry for 30 seconds.Now add the ground mixture and mix everything.Turn off the flame and add thick tamarind juice.Mix everything well and taste the sambal. Adjust salt if needed.Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style coconut sambal for dosa with red chilies.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '10'),
('Vegetable Rava Upm', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/11a-3.jpg', 'Toasted Semolina/Sooji/Rava - 250g, Carrot - 75g, Green bean - 30g, Leeks - 50g, Onion - 50g, Curry leaves - Few, Butter - 1 tablespoon, Thin coconut milk - 400ml, Dried red chili - 2 or 3, Mustard seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ¼ teaspoon, Salt - As you wish, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Take the carrot, green bean, and leeks. Clean and wash them well. (Refer Note 1)Chop the carrot, green bean, leeks, and onion.Chop the dried red chili and curry leaves. In addition, get ready with salt, turmeric powder, mustard seeds, and toasted semolina. (Refer Note 2)Extract the thin coconut milk and take the butter. (Refer Note 3)First of all, heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let it splutter. Now add curry leaves, and dried red chilies. Fry them for 30 seconds.Add the onions, green bean, and carrot. Stir and cook uncovered under medium flame for about 3 minutes.Add chopped leeks. Stir and cook on medium flame for about 30 seconds.Now add butter, salt, turmeric powder, and thin coconut milk.Mix everything well and cook uncovered under high flame until the milk foams up. For me, the milk has foamed up in a minute.Now turn the flame to low and add the toasted semolina. As soon as you add the semolina, stir and mix as quickly as you can. Constantly stir and mix everything under low flame for about 2 minutes.Finally, switch off the flame, stir, and mix repeatedly for a minute. (Refer Note 4)Taste and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make vegetable Rava Upma at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style mixed vegetable Rava Upma.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '10'),
('Lady’s Finger Milk Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/7a-3.jpg', 'Okra/Ladies finger - 125g, Tomato - 125g, Large onion - ½, Green chilies - 2 or 3, Thin coconut milk - 250ml, Salt - As you need, Turmeric powder - ¼ teaspoon, Curry leaves - Few', 'Take the okra, tomato and rinse it well. Cut the okra into about 2-inch pieces and slice the tomato.Chop the onions and slice the green chilies. Get ready with curry leaves, turmeric powder, and salt. Also, extract thin coconut milk from grated coconut. (Refer Note 1)Place the cooking pan on the stove. Add okra pieces, sliced tomatoes, chopped onions, curry leaves, sliced green chilies, turmeric powder, and salt.Add the coconut milk and mix everything well. Now switch on the flame.Cook covered under the high flame for 6 to 8 minutes.Open the lid, stirs, mix everything, and again cook covered under medium flame for 5 to 7 minutes.Open the lid, taste the curry, and adjust salt if needed.Serve and enjoy this healthy okra tomato coconut curry recipe in Sri Lankan style.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '15');
