('Vegetable Fried Rice', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/14a.jpg', 'Basmati rice - 350g, Soy meat - 25g (Optional), Carrot - 100g, Leeks - 75g, Green bean - 75g, Onion - 125g, Garlic paste - 1 teaspoon, Ginger paste - ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ¼ teaspoon, Curry leaves - 2 sprigs, Salt - As you wish, Cooking oil - As you wish', 'Wash the rice and boil it. Add little oil and salt when boiling the rice. The boiled rice should soft but not sticky or soggy.Add soy meat and water in a bowl. Let the soy meat to soak for 30 minutes. Then strain all the water and cut them into half. Add salt, mix them well, and keep it aside.Cut the carrot, onion, green bean, and leek. Also, take some curry leaves.Get ready with garlic paste, ginger paste, turmeric powder, and salt.Heat the oil in deep fry wok and add curry leaves. Stir and fry them for 20 to 30 seconds. Once done, put them on top of the boiled rice.Fry the onion under the high flame until it turns into brown color. For me, it takes about 5 minutes. Put them on top of the rice.Fry the soy meat under the high flame until it turns into light brown. For me, it takes about 3 minutes. Once done, put them on top of the rice.Now, heat the oil in a cooking pan and add green bean. Cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burn. Then, add the carrot and cook uncovered under medium flame for 3 or 4 minutes. Stir occasionally.Add leeks, salt, and turmeric powder. Stir, mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes.Finally, add ginger and garlic pastes. Cook uncovered under medium flame for 1 minute. Stir constantly to avoid burn.Now put the vegetable mixture too on top of the boiled rice. So now you have the boiled rice, fried curry leaves, onions, soy meat, and vegetable mixture.Mix them well till totally combined.Taste the rice and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make vegetable fried rice in a quick and easy way. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style healthy vegetable fried rice without soya sauce and eggs.', 'vegetarian', 'nonspicy', '35 '),
('White Puttu', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/7a.jpg', 'Steamed all-purpose flour - 750g, Hot water - 625ml, Salt - As you need, Grated coconut - As you need', 'Take the steamed all-purpose flour. Also, add salt in the hot water, give a stir, and keep aside.Add the salt-mixed-hot-water little by little while mixing the flour. Mix well to small thick pieces.Now put those on a flat surface and use a sharp edge cup or tin to make them crumble. Besides, get ready with the grated coconut.Place the puttu steamer on the stove and boil the water until the steam comes out from the top of the steamer.Now take off the top of the steamer and fill that with the dry crumble mixture and grated coconut. I fill that in the following way. Grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut.Cook till steam comes out through the top of the steamer. For me, it takes about 2 minutes for each batch.Once done, unmold the puttu.This is how to make the white puttu recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style all-purpose flour puttu with curries.', 'nonvegetarian', 'nonspicy', '20'),
('Spicy Tinned Fish Sandwich Toast Recipe with Potato Masala', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/15a.jpg', 'Tinned fish - 285g (Only Fish Chunks), Bread - 20 slices, Butter - As you wish, Potato - 500g, Onion - 200g, Garlic cloves - 5 or 6, Dried red chili - 20 to 25 (about 25g), Curry leaves - Few, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you need, Cooking oil - As you need, Lime - ½ Large, Water - 100ml', 'Take the tin fish, open it, drain all the liquid, and take off the fish chunks.Make the dried red chili flakes. Also, get ready with mustard seeds, turmeric powder, salt, and lime.Boil the potatoes and peel off the skin. Also, chop the onions, mince the garlic and chop the curry leaves.Heat the oil in a cooking wok. Add mustard seeds and let it splutter. Then add the onion and curry leaves. Fry them under high flame until the onion has softened and turned translucent for about 3 minutes. Now add minced garlic. Mix and fry them until the onion starts turn to golden color.Now add salt and turmeric powder. Mix and fry them under medium flame for 1 or 2 minutes.Add the tinned fish chunks, dried red chili flakes, and water.Mix everything well and cook covered under low flame for about 5 minutes.Now add the boiled potatoes.Mash the potatoes and tinned fish chunks well enough.Finally, switch off the flame, add lime juice, and give one last good mix.Taste the curry and adjust salt, lime, red chili flakes if needed.Fill the curry between 2 slices of bread.Grease the sandwich toaster with the melted butter.Place the bread inside the sandwich toaster.Close the toaster tightly and toast the bread. Different toasters require different time to toast the bread. For me, it takes about 5 minutes to toast the bread.This is how to make the best spicy tinned fish sandwich toast recipe in Sri Lankan style. Serve and enjoy this bread sandwich toast.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '55'),
('Chicken Kottu Roti', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/20a.jpg', '-----For Chicken Curry-----Chicken - 1kg, Tomato - 300g, Onion - 100g, Garlic paste - 1 tablespoon, Ginger paste - ½ tablespoon, Curry powder - 3 tablespoons, Cardamom - 4, Crushed cinnamon - ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - 1 teaspoon, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Curry leaves - Few, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you need, Water - 500ml-----For Kottu Roti-----Parotta/Paratha Roti - 20, Eggs - 10, Carrot - 250g, Leek - 150g, Banana pepper - 100g, Onion - 250g, Green chili - 10 to 12, Curry leaves - 2 or 3 sprigs, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you want', 'For the chicken curry chop the onion and slice the tomatoes. Also, prepare the ginger and garlic paste. Additionally, take curry leaves, water, curry powder, cardamom, cinnamon, mustard seeds, turmeric powder, and salt.Rinse the chicken and add turmeric powder, salt, and ginger-garlic paste. Mix and marinate for 30 minutes.Heat the oil, add mustard seeds, and let them splutter. Then add onion and curry leaves. Sauté until onion turns translucent. Now add crushed cardamom and cinnamon. Sauté them until the onion start turns to golden.Add the tomato and sauté them for 2 or 3 minutes.Now add marinated chicken, mix well, and cook covered under high flame for 5 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good mix, and again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates. For me, it takes about 10 minutes.Now, take off the lid and cook uncovered under medium flame until the chicken pieces get bit-fried. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 4 minutes. Then, add curry powder and water. Mix well.Cook covered under high flame for 3 or 4 minutes.Then take off the lid, give one last good stir, and again cook covered under very low flame for 5 minutes. Taste the gravy and adjust salt if needed. This is how to make the best chicken curry for Kottu Roti.Cut the parotta into tiny pieces.Slice the carrot, banana pepper, and leek. Also, chop the onion, green chili, and curry leaves.Add a little salt to the eggs and whisk them for 2 or 3 minutes.Now heat the oil in a large cooking wok and add the beaten eggs. Fry and scramble the eggs. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under medium flame. Once done, take off the scrambled eggs and keep them aside for final preparation.Now, add some more oil to the same large cooking wok. Add carrot, banana pepper, half of the chopped onions, green chilies, and curry leaves.Sauté those until carrots turn tender. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under high flame.Then add the leeks and sauté them under medium flame for 2 minutes.Now add parotta and chicken curry. Stir and mix frequently under medium flame for about 2 or 3 minutes. Taste and adjust salt if needed.Finally, add fried scrambled eggs and the rest of the chopped onion. Switch off the flame and mix everything well until totally combined.This is how to make the best chicken kottu rotti recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan chicken kothu parotta dish with your friends and family.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20'),
('Mixed Vegetable Roti', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/14a.jpg', 'All-purpose flour - 1kg, Green bean - 40g, Carrot - 50g, Leeks - 50g, Green chili - 50g, Onion - 175g, Grated coconut - 200g, Baking powder - 1 teaspoon, Sugar - 1 tablespoon, Salt - As you wish, Water - 400ml, Cooking oil - 4 tablespoons', 'Take the green bean, leeks, carrots, green chilies, and onions. Clean and wash them well. Chop them into small pieces.Get ready with grated coconut, salt, sugar, baking powder, and water.Take a large bowl and add all purpose flour. Also, add salt, baking powder, and sugar. Mix them well till totally combined.Now add carrot, green bean, leeks, green chili, onion, and grated coconut.Mix them well and add the water.Mix everything well using your fingers, knuckles, and palm.Knead the dough for 4 or 5 minutes. The dough should smooth and soft. Add water or flour as needed to adjust consistency.Now add the cooking oil.Again knead the dough for 1 or 2 minutes. The dough should smooth and elastic but not sticky.Now make the balls as you want and keep them aside for at least 1 hour before making the roti.Grease a little oil on a floured surface. On the floured surface, use the rolling pin to roll out the balls until very thin.Heat the skillet and place the thin dough layer on it. Flip and cook on the other side. It took one minute for each side under low flame.This is how to make mixed vegetable roti recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style simple vegetarian roti.', 'vegetarian', 'spicy', '30'),
('Red Rice Flour Puttu', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/10a.jpg', 'Roasted red rice flour - 600g, Hot water - 700ml, Salt - As you need, Grated coconut - As you wish', 'Take the roasted red rice flour.Add salt in the hot water and mix well.Add the salt-mixed-hot-water little by little while mixing the flour.Mix well to small thick pieces.Now put those on a flat surface and using a sharp edge cup or tin make them to a crumble texture.Get ready with the grated coconut.Place the puttu steamer on the stove and boil the water until the steam comes out from the top of the steamer.Now take off the top of the steamer and fill that with the dry crumble mixture and grated coconut. I fill that in the following way. Grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut -> dry crumble dough -> grated coconut.Steam it till the steam comes out through the top of the steamer. For me, it takes about 4 minutes.Once done, unmold the puttu.This is how to make the simple red rice flour puttu recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style red rice flour puttu with curries.', 'vegetarian', 'nonspicy', '25 '),
('Prawn Fried Noodles', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/12a.jpg', 'Noodle - 400g, Prawn/Shrimp - 300g (After clean), Carrot - 150g, Leeks - 75g, Cabbage - 75g, Green bean - 75g, Onion - 150g, Curry leaves - 3 sprigs, Garlic paste - 2 teaspoons, Ginger paste - 1 teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ + ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you need, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Clean the shrimps and rinse them thoroughly. Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix well and let them marinate for 30 minutes.Slice the carrot, cabbage, leeks, green beans, and onions. Also, get read with curry leaves, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, and salt.Boil the noodles and put them in a flat tray. The noodles should be soft and chewy, but not mushy or soggy.Fry the onions till golden brown. For me, it takes about five minutes.Fry the curry leaves. It takes about 30 seconds.Also, fry the marinated prawns till they start turning brown. For me, it takes about five minutes.Now, place a skillet on the stove. Add carrot, cabbage, green beans, turmeric powder, cooking oil, and salt. Give a good mix and switch on the flame.Cook covered under medium flame for about five minutes. In halfway through open the lid and give a good stir to avoid burning.Add leeks and ginger-garlic paste. Mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for two minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.So, now you have the boiled noodles, fried onions, fried curry leaves, fried prawns, and vegetable mix.Using two forks mix them until totally combined. Taste and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the best prawn fried noodles recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style delicious fried shrimp noodles.', 'nonvegetarian', 'nonspicy', '40 '),
('Fry Fish', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5a.jpg', 'Fish - 6 pieces (500g)Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoonChili powder - ½ teaspoonSalt - As you needCooking oil - As needed', 'Take the fish pieces and rinse them well.Add turmeric powder, chili powder, and salt. Mix well and let them marinate for at least 30 minutes.Heat the oil in a deep frying pan and fry the fish pieces.Fry the fish pieces until they turn to golden. If you wish, decorate them with onions, green chilies, and lime.This is how to make a simple deep fry fish recipe without egg or flour. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style easy fish fry dish.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '10 '),
('Chicken Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11a.jpg', 'Chicken - 1kg, Tomato - 250g, Onion - 150g, Garlic paste - 1 tablespoon, Ginger paste - ½ tablespoon, Curry powder - 3 tablespoons, Cardamom - 4, Crushed cinnamon - ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - 1 teaspoon, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Curry leaves - Few, Salt - As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt), Cooking oil - As you need (KETO people use the Organic Coconut Oil), Water - 500ml', 'Slice the tomatoes and chop the onions. Also, prepare the ginger and garlic paste. Additionally, get ready with curry leaves, water, curry powder, turmeric powder, mustard seeds, cardamom, cinnamon, and salt.Cut the chicken into your desired size pieces and rinse them well. Add turmeric powder, salt, ginger paste, and garlic paste. Mix well and let them marinate for at least 30 minutes.Heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then add the onions and curry leaves. Sauté till onions turn to translucent. For me, it takes about 2 minutes. Now, add the crushed cardamom and cinnamon. Stir and fry them till onions turn golden.Add tomatoes and cook them under high flame for about 2 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.Now add the marinated chicken pieces and give a good mix until all combined.Cook covered under high flame for 5 minutes.Take off the lid and give a good gentle stir. Again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates. For me, it takes about 10 minutes.Now take off the lid and cook uncovered under medium flame until the chicken pieces get bit fried. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 4 minutes. Then add the curry powder and water. Mix them well.Cook covered under high flame for 3 to 4 minutes.Take off the lid, give a gentle stir, and again cook covered under very low flame for about 5 minutes.Taste the gravy and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make an easy chicken curry without coconut milk or cream. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style simple spicy chicken curry.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '30 '),
('Prawn Fried Noodles', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/12a.jpg', 'Noodle - 400g, Prawn/Shrimp - 300g (After clean), Carrot - 150g, Leeks - 75g, Cabbage - 75g, Green bean - 75g, Onion - 150g, Curry leaves - 3 sprigs, Garlic paste - 2 teaspoons, Ginger paste - 1 teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ + ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you need, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Clean the shrimps and rinse them thoroughly. Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix well and let them marinate for 30 minutes.Slice the carrot, cabbage, leeks, green beans, and onions. Also, get read with curry leaves, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, and salt.Boil the noodles and put them in a flat tray. The noodles should be soft and chewy, but not mushy or soggy.Fry the onions till golden brown. For me, it takes about five minutes.Fry the curry leaves. It takes about 30 seconds.Also, fry the marinated prawns till they start turning brown. For me, it takes about five minutes.Now, place a skillet on the stove. Add carrot, cabbage, green beans, turmeric powder, cooking oil, and salt. Give a good mix and switch on the flame.Cook covered under medium flame for about five minutes. In halfway through open the lid and give a good stir to avoid burning.Add leeks and ginger-garlic paste. Mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for two minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.So, now you have the boiled noodles, fried onions, fried curry leaves, fried prawns, and vegetable mix.Using two forks mix them until totally combined. Taste and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the best prawn fried noodles recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style delicious fried shrimp noodles.', 'nonvegetarian', 'nonspicy', '40 '),
('Mutton Blood Fry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6a.jpg', 'Mutton Blood - 650g, Shallots/Small onion - 200g, Green chili - 2 or 3, Dried red chili - 4 or 5, Curry leaves - 2 or 3 sprigs, Turmeric powder - 1 teaspoon, Fennel seeds - 1 tablespoon, Mustard seeds - 1 teaspoon, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you want', 'Place a skillet on the stove and add mutton blood, turmeric powder, and salt.Mix, stir, and cook under medium flame until blood turns dark brown. Using a spoon break the blood into a crumble texture. Mix and stir constantly to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 12 minutes. Once done, take off the boiled-crumble-textured-mutton-blood and leave it aside for final preparation.Cut the shallots, green chilies, and dried red chilies into small pieces. Besides, get ready with curry leaves, fennel seeds, mustard seeds, and cooking oil.Heat the oil in the skillet and add onions. Sauté them till onions turn translucent. Then, add curry leaves and sauté them for 15 seconds. Now, add dried red chili and sauté them for another 15 seconds. Then, add fennel seeds and mustard seeds. Sauté them till onion starts turn to golden. Finally, add green chili and sauté them for 15 seconds.Now, add boiled-crumble-textured-mutton-blood and give a good mix till all are combined.This is how to cook mutton blood fry in Sri Lankan style. Serve and enjoy this Goat blood fry alone or with bread.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20 '),
('Deviled Chicken', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/9a.jpg', 'Chicken - 750g, Onion - 250g, Tomato - 150g, Banana pepper - 100g, Green chili - 4 or 5, Curry leaves - 2 sprigs, Lime - ½, Garlic paste - 1 tablespoon, Minced garlic - 1 tablespoon, Ginger paste - ½ tablespoon, Minced ginger - ¾ tablespoon, Red chili flakes - 1 tablespoon, Crushed black pepper - ½ tablespoo, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Tomato sauce - As you want, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you want', 'Clean, rinse, and cut the chicken into medium-sized pieces. Add ginger and garlic pastes, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix and let them marinate for 30 minutes.Cook the marinated chicken covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates or 15 minutes, whichever comes first. In halfway through open the lid and give a stir to avoid burning.Fry the cooked chicken pieces to golden.Cut the onions, tomatoes, and banana peppers into medium-sized pieces. Also, half the green chilies and mince the ginger and garlic. Besides, get ready with curry leaves, lime, tomato sauce, red chili flakes, and crushed black pepper.Heat the oil in a pan and add minced ginger, minced garlic, curry leaves, and green chilies. Sauté them for one minute under high flame.Then, add onion, tomato, and banana pepper. Sauté them for two minutes under high flame. Stir frequently.Now, add fried chicken pieces, red chili flakes, and crushed black pepper. Mix and stir them for one minute under a low flame.Add some salt and tomato sauce. Give a good mix until all combined under low flame.Finally, switch off the flame and add the lime juice. Give one last good mix.This is how to make the best deviled chicken recipe in Sri Lankan style. Serve and enjoy this easy delicious devilled chicken.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '10 '),
('Spicy Chicken Thick Gravy', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12a.jpg', '-----For Chicken Curry-----Chicken - 1250g, Onion - 125g, Tomato - 250g, Garlic paste - 1 ½ tablespoon, Ginger paste - ¾ tablespoon, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ¾ teaspoon, Curry leaves - Few, Water - 150ml, Salt - As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt), Cooking oil - As you want (KETO people use the Organic Coconut Oil)-----For Curry Powder-----Dried red chili - 10 to 12, Coriander seeds - 1 tablespoon, Black pepper - 1 tablespoon, Fennel seeds - ¾ tablespoon, Cumin seeds - ¼ tablespoon, Cardamom - 5, Crushed cinnamon - 1 tablespoon, Curry leaves - 1 sprig', 'Take a skillet and dry roast dried red chili, coriander seeds, black pepper, fennel seeds, cumin seeds, cardamom, cinnamon, and curry leaves. I roast them under low flame for 5 minutes. Then grind them to a fine powder.Chop the onions and slice the tomatoes. Also, prepare the ginger and garlic paste. Additionally, get ready with curry leaves, mustard seeds, salt, turmeric powder, ground curry powder, and water.Rinse the chicken well enough. Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix well and let them marinate for at least 30 minutes.Heat the oil in a cooking wok and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then add onions and curry leaves. Sauté those until onions turn golden.Now, add tomatoes and sauté until tomatoes turn tender. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under high flame.Add marinated chicken pieces along with ginger and garlic paste. Mix well until all combined.Cook covered under high flame for 5 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good stir, and again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates or 10 minutes whichever comes first.Then cook uncovered until the chicken pieces get a bit fried. Stir frequently to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 8 minutes under medium flame.Now, add ground curry powder and water.Give a gentle mix and stir occasionally under medium flame until you get good thick gravy. For me, it takes about 6 minutes.This is how to make the best spicy chicken thick gravy recipe without coconut milk. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style thick gravy spicy chicken curry.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '40 '),
('Chicken Kottu Roti Recipe', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/20a.jpg', '-----For Chicken Curry-----Chicken - 1kg, Tomato - 300g, Onion - 100g, Garlic paste - 1 tablespoon, Ginger paste - ½ tablespoon, Curry powder - 3 tablespoons, Cardamom - 4, Crushed cinnamon - ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - 1 teaspoon, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Curry leaves - Few, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you need, Water - 500ml-----For Kottu Roti-----Parotta/Paratha Roti - 20, Eggs - 10, Carrot - 250g, Leek - 150g, Banana pepper - 100g, Onion - 250g, Green chili - 10 to 12, Curry leaves - 2 or 3 sprigs, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you want', 'For the chicken curry chop the onion and slice the tomatoes. Also, prepare the ginger and garlic paste. Additionally, take curry leaves, water, curry powder, cardamom, cinnamon, mustard seeds, turmeric powder, and salt.Rinse the chicken and add turmeric powder, salt, and ginger-garlic paste. Mix and marinate for 30 minutes.Heat the oil, add mustard seeds, and let them splutter. Then add onion and curry leaves. Sauté until onion turns translucent. Now add crushed cardamom and cinnamon. Sauté them until the onion start turns to golden.Add the tomato and sauté them for 2 or 3 minutes.Now add marinated chicken, mix well, and cook covered under high flame for 5 minutes.Take off the lid, give a good mix, and again cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates. For me, it takes about 10 minutes.Now, take off the lid and cook uncovered under medium flame until the chicken pieces get bit-fried. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 4 minutes. Then, add curry powder and water. Mix well.Cook covered under high flame for 3 or 4 minutes.Then take off the lid, give one last good stir, and again cook covered under very low flame for 5 minutes. Taste the gravy and adjust salt if needed. This is how to make the best chicken curry for Kottu Roti.Cut the parotta into tiny pieces.Slice the carrot, banana pepper, and leek. Also, chop the onion, green chili, and curry leaves.Add a little salt to the eggs and whisk them for 2 or 3 minutes.Now heat the oil in a large cooking wok and add the beaten eggs. Fry and scramble the eggs. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under medium flame. Once done, take off the scrambled eggs and keep them aside for final preparation.Now, add some more oil to the same large cooking wok. Add carrot, banana pepper, half of the chopped onions, green chilies, and curry leaves.Sauté those until carrots turn tender. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 5 minutes under high flame.Then add the leeks and sauté them under medium flame for 2 minutes.Now add parotta and chicken curry. Stir and mix frequently under medium flame for about 2 or 3 minutes. Taste and adjust salt if needed.Finally, add fried scrambled eggs and the rest of the chopped onion. Switch off the flame and mix everything well until totally combined.This is how to make the best chicken kottu rotti recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan chicken kothu parotta dish with your friends and family.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20'),
('Spicy Beef Oxtail Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/10a.jpg', 'Beef oxtail - 1kg, Tomato - 250g, Onion - 150g, Garlic paste - 1 tablespoon, Ginger paste - ½ tablespoon, Curry powder - 3 tablespoons, Curry leaves - Few, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Water - As you want, Salt - As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt), Cooking oil - As you want (KETO people use the Organic Coconut Oil)', 'Take the oxtail, wash them thoroughly, and add garlic paste, ginger paste, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix well and let marinate for 30 minutes.Slice the tomatoes and onions. Besides, get ready with curry leaves, mustard seeds, curry powder, cooking oil, and water.Heat the oil, add mustard seeds, and let them splutter. Then, add onion and curry leaves. Sauté them till onion turns to golden.Now, add tomatoes and sauté them under high flame until tomatoes turn soft and juicy. For me, it takes about 6 minutes.Add the marinated beef oxtail and mix them well.Cook covered under the high flame until all the liquid evaporates. In halfway through take off the lid and give a stir to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 12 minutes.Now, take off the lid and cook uncovered under medium flame until beef oxtails get a bit fried. Stir occasionally to avoid burning. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Now, add curry powder and water. Give a good mix.Cook covered under high flame for 2 minutes.Take off the lid, give a mix, taste the curry, and adjust salt or curry powder if needed. Finally, cook covered under a very low flame for about 30 minutes.This is how to make the best and spicy beef oxtail curry recipe without wine or coconut. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style beef oxtail curry.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '59'),
('Babath Curry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10a.jpg', 'Mutton boti – 1kg, Onion - 100g, Chopped ginger - 1 tablespoon, Curry powder - 3 tablespoons, Turmeric powder - 1 teaspoon, Mustard seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Cardamom - 4 or 5, Crushed cinnamon - ½ tablespoon, Curry leaves - Few, Thick coconut milk - 300ml, Lime - ½, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you want', 'Take the mutton boti/intestine, clean, and rinse them well 2 or 3 times. Add turmeric powder, salt, cardamom, and cinnamon. Give a good mix.Cook covered under the high flame until mutton boti turns tender and all the liquid evaporates. In halfway through, open the lid and give a good stir. For me, it takes about 30 minutes.Once the cooked boti cools down, cut them into small pieces.Cut the onion and mince the ginger. Also, prepare the thick coconut milk. Besides, get ready with curry leaves, lime, mustard seeds, curry powder, salt, and cooking oil.Heat the oil and add mustard seeds. Let them splutter. Then add onion and curry leaves. Sauté them till the onion starts turn to golden.Now add the cooked mutton boti. Give a good mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for 6 to 8 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.Now, add curry powder, salt, and coconut milk. Give a good mix.Cook covered under medium flame for 5 minutes.Finally, switch off the flame, add ginger, and squeeze the lime. Give one last good mix. Adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a spicy mutton boti curry recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style babath curry dish.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20 '),
('Chicken and Egg Soup', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/15a.jpg', 'Boneless chicken - 350g, Carrot - 250g, Green bean - 125g, Egg - 4 or 5, Cornstarch - 150g, Crushed black pepper - 1 ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - ½ + ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you want, Water - 4 liters', 'Slice the carrot and green beans. Take the boneless chicken and rinse them thoroughly. Also, get ready with cornstarch, eggs, crushed black pepper, turmeric powder, water, and salt.Place the chicken in a cooking pot and add ½ teaspoon of turmeric powder, salt, and water. Boil the chicken until it gets tender. For me, it takes about 10 minutes. Keep the rest of the chicken-boiled water and the cooking pot for making the soup.Once the chicken gets cool down tear it to tiny pieces.Now switch on the flame and add carrot, green beans, ½ teaspoon turmeric powder, and salt in the same cooking pot where you boiled the chicken.Also, add the rest of the water and boil them uncovered under high flame for about 20 minutes.Meanwhile, whisk the eggs and take the cornstarch in a bowl.Now, add the boiled chicken pieces, mix, and cook uncovered under medium flame for about 10 minutes.Add the boiled soup water to the cornstarch.Mix the cornstarch and water until cornstarch has dissolved thoroughly.Now pour the cornstarch into the soup.Mix thoroughly until all dissolve.Add the egg while stirring the soup. Cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 or 3 minutes. Stir occasionally.Give a good mix and taste the soup. Adjust salt if needed.Finally, switch off the flame, add the crushed black pepper and give one last good mix.This is how to make an easy chicken and egg soup with cornstarch. Serve and enjoy this tasty chicken and egg soup without broth.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '45'),
('Beef Rolls', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/14a.jpg', 'Beef - 850g, Potato - 300g, Onion - 300g, Garlic cloves - 5 to 7, Ginger - Small size (about the size of one large garlic clove), Green chili - 4 to 6, Curry leaves - Few, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you want, Red chili powder - 1 tablespoon, Coriander powder - 2 teaspoons, Lemon - ½, Egg - 5, Breadcrumbs - 250g, Spring roll wrapper - 50 (6” or 150mm square sheet), Cooking oil - As you need', 'Take the beef, rinse well, and cut it into tiny pieces. Also, chop the potatoes and onions.Get ready with minced garlic and ginger, chopped green chilies and curry leaves, turmeric powder, salt, red chili powder, coriander powder, and lemon.Heat the oil and add ¾ of the chopped onions. Fry them until translucent. Then add green chilies and curry leaves. Fry them until onions turn to light brown color.Now add the beef, ginger, garlic, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix them well.Cook covered under high flame for 5 to 7 minutes. Then take off the lid, give a good stir, and again cook covered under medium flame for 3 to 5 minutes.Add potatoes, red chili powder, and coriander powder. Mix them well.Cook covered under low flame until the potatoes get boiled. For me, it takes about 6 minutes.Finally, switch off the flame and rest of the onions and lemon.Adjust salt if needed and give a good one last mix.Once the curry comes to room temperature make the rolls with the help of spring roll wrappers.Whisk the eggs with some salt and take the breadcrumbs. First, dip the roll into the egg and then coat the roll with breadcrumbs. Again soak it in the egg and then coat with the breadcrumbs.Do the same to all of the rolls.Now heat the oil in a deep frying pan and fry the rolls. Do this in a semi-medium flame. Once the rolls turn to brown color, take them out.This is how to make beef rolls recipe at home in Sri Lankan style. Serve and enjoy these tasty and crispy beef rolls.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '30 '),
('Fish Head Curry Spicy', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/11a.jpg', 'Fish headpieces - 500g, Onion - 50g, Thin tamarind juice - 200ml, Thin coconut milk - 400ml, Garlic cloves - 3 to 5, Curry leaves - Few, Curry powder - 1 ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Fenugreek seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Salt - As you wish', 'Take the fish head pieces and wash them thoroughly. I strongly recommend you use a large head from a single fish. I use the head of a large sea bass fish.Chop the onions and garlic. Also, get ready with curry leaves, curry powder, turmeric powder, fenugreek seeds, and salt.Prepare the thin coconut milk and tamarind juice.Place the cooking wok on the stove and add onions, garlic, and curry leaves. Switch on the flame and dry roast them under low flame for about 3 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.Add fenugreek seeds and keep dry roast them for another 2 minutes under low flame.Now add curry powder, turmeric powder, and salt.Then add the coconut milk.Additionally, add the tamarind juice.Finally, add the pieces of the fish head.Mix everything and cook covered under the semi-high flame for 10 to 12 minutes.Take off the lid and give a gentle stir. Again cook covered under very low flame for about 5 minutes.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a simple fish head curry recipe without a single drop of oil. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style spicy fish head curry dish.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Simple Chicken Fry', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/6a-1.jpg', 'Chicken - 1250g, Hot & spicy chicken fry mix powder - 4 tablespoons, Chili powder - 1 tablespoon, Water - 100ml, Salt - As you want, Lime - As you want (Optional), Onion - As you want (Optional)', 'Rinse the chicken pieces and score them.Add hot and spicy chicken fry mix powder. I used the KTC brand hot and spicy chicken fry mix powder. If you are in the United Kingdom, you can easily find this powder in the ASDA store. If not, try this powder in Amazon. Or else, you can use a different hot and spicy chicken fry mix powder.On top of that, add chili powder, salt, and water.Using your fingers mix well until totally combined. Let them marinate for at least 2 hours. After 2 hours, mix again before frying them.Heat the oil in a deep frying pan. Once the oil gets maximum heat, turn the flame to medium and fry the chicken pieces. It may take about 10 minutes for each trip.This is how to make the best and simple chicken fry recipe at home. Serve and enjoy this delicious crispy chicken fry with raw onions and lime.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '30 '),
('Sri Lankan Fish Sothi', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/9a-1.jpg', 'Fish - 500g, Tomato - 200g, Onion - 75g, Green chili - 3 or 4, Lime - ½, Curry leaves - Few, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Fenugreek seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Thick coconut milk - 300ml, Thin coconut milk - 600ml, Salt - As you want (KETO people use the Himalayan Pink Salt)', 'Take the fish pieces and rinse them thoroughly. Also, get ready with turmeric powder, salt, and fenugreek seeds.Slice the tomatoes and green chilies. Also, chop the onions. Take curry leaves and lime.Get ready with thick and thin coconut milk.Place the cooking wok on the stove. Add the fish pieces, turmeric powder, fenugreek seeds, and salt. On top of that add onion, green chilies, curry leaves, and thin coconut milk. Mix them well.Cook covered under high flame for about 10 minutes. Then take off the lid and add tomatoes. Give a good mix.Cook covered under high flame for about 5 minutes. Then add the thick coconut milk. Mix well.Cook uncovered under high flame for 2 or 3 minutes. Stir occasionally, but gently.Finally, switch off the flame and add the lime juice. Give one last good mix gently.Taste the sothi and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make a simple Sri Lankan fish sothi recipe with tomatoes. Serve and enjoy this keto-friendly fish sothi.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '25'),
('Spicy Tinned Fish Sandwich Toast Recipe with Potato Masala', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/15a.jpg', 'Tinned fish - 285g (Only Fish Chunks), Bread - 20 slices, Butter - As you wish, Potato - 500g, Onion - 200g, Garlic cloves - 5 or 6, Dried red chili - 20 to 25 (about 25g), Curry leaves - Few, Mustard seeds - ½ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Salt - As you need, Cooking oil - As you need, Lime - ½ LargeWater - 100ml', 'Take the tin fish, open it, drain all the liquid, and take off the fish chunks.Make the dried red chili flakes. Also, get ready with mustard seeds, turmeric powder, salt, and lime.Boil the potatoes and peel off the skin. Also, chop the onions, mince the garlic and chop the curry leaves.Heat the oil in a cooking wok. Add mustard seeds and let it splutter. Then add the onion and curry leaves. Fry them under high flame until the onion has softened and turned translucent for about 3 minutes. Now add minced garlic. Mix and fry them until the onion starts turn to golden color.Now add salt and turmeric powder. Mix and fry them under medium flame for 1 or 2 minutes.Add the tinned fish chunks, dried red chili flakes, and water.Mix everything well and cook covered under low flame for about 5 minutes.Now add the boiled potatoes.Mash the potatoes and tinned fish chunks well enough.Finally, switch off the flame, add lime juice, and give one last good mix.Taste the curry and adjust salt, lime, red chili flakes if needed.Fill the curry between 2 slices of bread.Grease the sandwich toaster with the melted butter.Place the bread inside the sandwich toaster.Close the toaster tightly and toast the bread. Different toasters require different time to toast the bread. For me, it takes about 5 minutes to toast the bread.This is how to make the best spicy tinned fish sandwich toast recipe in Sri Lankan style. Serve and enjoy this bread sandwich toast.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '57'),
('Beef Biryani Recipe with Potatoes', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/17a.jpg', 'Beef - 500g, Potatoes - 250g, Basmati rice - 350g, Onion - 100g, Green chili - 6 to 8, Garlic clove - 4 to 6, Ginger root - Small (About the size of 1 garlic clove), Thick coconut milk - 300ml, Curry leaves - Few, Fennel seeds - 1 tablespoon, Cumin seeds - ½ teaspoon, Black pepper - 1 tablespoon, Coriander seeds - 1 teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Cardamom - 6 to 8, Crushed cinnamon - ½ tablespoon, Salt - As you need, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Take the beef and cut into medium-sized pieces. Rinse them well and keep aside.Take the grinder and add black pepper, fennel seeds, cumin seeds, coriander seeds, garlic cloves, ginger, and a little water. Also, get ready with turmeric powder and salt.Grind them to smooth paste.Now add turmeric powder, salt, and ground mixture to the beef.Mix well and let them marinate for at least an hour.Chop the onion, cut the green chilies by half, and crush the cinnamon. Also, get ready with curry leaves and cardamom. Besides, extract the thick coconut milk from grated coconut.Slice the potatoes into medium size. Also, get ready with basmati rice.Heat the oil, add cardamom and cinnamon. Sauté them for 10 to 20 seconds. I suggest you use a large non-stick cooking pot with a lid.Now add the onions, curry leaves, and green chilies. Fry them under high flame until the onion starts to turn a golden color. Stir occasionally to avoid burn. For me, it takes about 3 minutes.Add the marinated beef and mix them well. Cook covered under the high flame for 6 to 8 minutes.Take off the lid and add potatoes. Now add the coconut milk and mix them well. Also, taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.Cook covered under medium flame until you get a well-cooked beef with little gravy. For me, it takes about 15 minutes.While you cook the beef, wash the basmati rice and boil it. It is enough to boil the rice for 90%.Once the rice 90% done, strain the water and add all the rice on top of the beef curry. Spread it evenly.Finally, cook covered under very low flame for 6 to 8 minutes.Switch off the flame and mix everything well until all combined.This is how to make Sri Lankan beef biryani recipe with potatoes. Serve and enjoy this delicious Sri Lankan style beef biryani.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '45 '),
('Chicken Samosa', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/21a.jpg', 'Boneless chicken - 500g, Potato - 350g, Onion - 250g, Spring roll paper - 20 sheets, Green chili - 4 to 6, Garlic clove - 4 to 6, Mustard seeds - ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Chili powder - 1 tablespoon, Crushed cinnamon - ¾ teaspoon, Cardamom - 3 or 4, Curry leaves - Few, Water - 100ml, Salt - As you wish, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Take the boneless chicken and cut it into large pieces. Rinse them well and add cinnamon, cardamom, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix everything well and place it on the stove.Cook covered under high flame till the chicken turns to tender. For me, it takes about 12 minutes. In a halfway through, or after 6 minutes take off the lid and give a good stir. You don’t need to add water, but if you feel the chicken starts to burn before it cooks well, you need to add some water.Let the chicken cool down before handling. Now tear the chicken into small pieces.Heat the oil in a deep fry pan and fry the chicken pieces under high flame. Fry them till it turns into little brown. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Dice the onion, green chilies, garlic cloves, and curry leaves.Also, dice the potatoes.Get ready with chili powder, mustard seeds, salt, and water.Heat the oil and add the mustard seeds. Let it splutter. Now add half of the onion and keep the rest aside for final preparation. Fry the onion under medium flame till it turns into translucent. For me, it takes about 2 minutes.Add garlic, curry leaves, and green chilies. Mix and fry them under medium flame until the onion start turns to brown color.Now add potato, chili powder, and salt. Also, add the water and mix them well.Cook covered under low flame until all the water disappears. For me, it takes about 5 minutes.Now add the fried chicken pieces and rest of the onion.Mix and cook uncovered under low flame for 1 or 2 minutes. Stir and mix constantly to avoid burn.Taste the curry and adjust salt if needed.Now take the spring roll paper and cut them into three symmetric pieces. If you use 20 spring roll papers, you will get 60 sheets after cut them into symmetric pieces. I used two sheets for each samosa. Hence, I made 30 samosas.Make the samosas.Heat the oil in a deep fry pan and add samosas. Fry them until the outer layer gets light brown color. Let the cooking oil gets maximum heat before place the samosas in it.This is the tastiest way to make chicken samosa recipe. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style crispy chicken samosa.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20 '),
('Fish Curry without Oil & Red Chil', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/12a-1.jpg', 'Fish - 400g, Onion - 50g, Thin coconut milk - 500ml, Garlic clove - 5 or 6, Ginger root - Small (About the size of one garlic clove), Green chili - 3 or 4, Curry Leaves - Few, Fennel seeds - 1 tablespoon, Cumin seeds/powder - ¼ teaspoon, Coriander seeds - ½ tablespoon, Turmeric powder - ½ teaspoon, Black pepper - 1 ½ tablespoon, Lime - ½, Salt - As you need', 'Cut the fish into your desired pieces, rinse it well and keep aside.Chop the onion. Also, get ready with salt, turmeric powder, curry leaves, lime, and green chilies.Prepare 500ml of thin coconut milk.Take the grinder and add black pepper, garlic clove, ginger root, fennel seeds, cumin seeds, coriander seeds, and a little water.Grind everything to a very smooth paste.Place the cooking pan over the stove. Add the fish, ground paste, chopped onion, green chilies, curry leaves, salt, and turmeric powder. Also, add the thin coconut milk and mix everything well.Now switch on the flame. Cook covered under medium flame for 5 to 7 minutes.Take off the lid and give a gentle stir. Again cook covered under low flame for 5 to 7 minutes.Switch off the flame and add the lime juice. Give one last gentle mix.Taste the gravy and adjust salt if needed.This is how to make the best healthy fish curry without oil and red chili powder. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style spicy fish curry.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '20 '),
('Shredded Chicken Fried Noodles with Vegetables', 'https://www.topsrilankanrecipe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/17a.jpg', 'Noodles - 400g, Boneless chicken - 400g, Carrot - 100g, Cabbage - 75g, Leeks - 75g, Banana pepper - 50g, Onion - 100g, Curry leaves - 2 sprigs, Garlic paste - 1 teaspoon, Ginger paste - ¼ teaspoon, Turmeric powder - ½ + ¼ teaspoons, Cardamom - 3 to 5, Crushed cinnamon - ¾ teaspoon, Salt - As you want, Cooking oil - As you need', 'Boil the noodles and spread it in a flat surface pan. The boiled noodles should be soft and chewy but not mushy or soggy.Take the boneless chicken and cut it into large pieces. Rinse them well and place them in a cooking pot. Add cinnamon, cardamom, ½ teaspoon of turmeric powder, and salt. Mix them well and switch on the flame.Cook covered under medium flame till the chicken turns to tender. For me, it takes about 12 minutes. Once in between takes of the lid and stir to avoid burn.Once done, let the chicken cool down and tear them into small pieces. Keep them aside for fry later.Take the carrot, leeks, banana pepper, and cabbage. Clean and rinse them well. Also, slice them.Slice the onion and take some curry leaves. Also, get ready with ginger paste, garlic paste, salt and ¼ teaspoon of turmeric powder.Heat the oil in a large deep fry pan and add the curry leaves. Fry them for 20 to 30 seconds under high flame. Put them on top of the noodles.Now, fry the onion under high flame till the onions start turns to brown color. For me, it takes about 5 minutes. Once done, put them on top of the noodles.At last, fry the shredded chicken pieces under medium flame till they start turns to little brown color. For me, it takes about 5 minutes. Add them on top of the noodles.Now, heat the oil in a cooking pot and add cabbage. Stir and cook covered under low flame for 2 or 3 minutes.Add carrot, stir, mix, and cook covered under low flame for 2 to 4 minutes.Now add leeks and banana pepper. Stir, mix and cook uncovered under medium flame for 2 to 4 minutes. Stir occasionally to avoid burning.Finally, add garlic paste, ginger paste, salt, turmeric powder. Stir, mix and cook uncovered under low flame for about 1 or 2 minutes. Add this vegetable mixture on top of the noodles.So, now you have the boiled noodles, fried curry leaves, fried onions, fried shredded chicken pieces, and cooked vegetable mixture.Mix them well until all combined.This is how to make shredded chicken fried noodles with vegetables. Serve and enjoy this Sri Lankan style fried chicken noodles without eggs and soy sauce.', 'nonvegetarian', 'spicy', '30 ');
